label: testis
definition: A gonad containing male germline stem cells which fuel sperm production. Testes are located dorsolaterally, and are excluded from the head. The neoblast compartment, including piwi-1+, nanos+ primordial germ cells, fuels formation of testes during juvenile development and regeneration.

label: nephridiopore
definition: The external opening and terminus of a protonephridium made by a terminal cell.

label: digestive tract lumen
definition: An anatomical space that is surrounded by a digestive tract.

label: pharynx inner epithelium
definition: Heavily ciliated epidermal cells covering the inner surface of the pharynx shaft.

label: dopaminergic neuron
definition: A neuron that expresses the neurotransmitter dopamine.

label: metaphase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: germ cell
definition: 1. A gamete (as an egg or sperm cell) or one of its antecedent cells. 2. A mature male or female germ cell usually possessing a haploid chromosome set and capable of initiating formation of a new diploid individual by fusion with a gamete of the opposite sex.

label: embryonic gut
definition: A cryptic digestive cavity comprised of phagocytic embryonic gut cells.

label: dorsal region of trunk fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment derived from pre- and post-pharyngeal amputations, encompassing the pharynx and parapharyngeal region.

label: eye
definition: An organ that detects light.

label: oviduct lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by the oviduct epithelium.

label: nuclear envelope
definition: The double lipid bilayer enclosing the nucleus and separating its contents from the rest of the cytoplasm; includes the intermembrane space, a gap of width 20-40 nm (also called the perinuclear space).

label: acidophilic gland cell
definition: One of two distinct histochemical classes of gland cells, these can be found throughout the body but primarily form clusters of subepidermal marginal adhesive glands along the dorsoventral border of the animal.

label: pharynx lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by the pharynx inner epithelium.

label: chemosensory neuron
definition: Any neuron that capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception.

label: sperm duct epithelium
definition: Ciliated epithelium lining the sperm duct.

label: cell
definition: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

label: epithelium
definition: The avascular cellular layers that cover body surfaces and cavities and may form glands.

label: anaphase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: ventral epidermis progenitor cell
definition: A progenitor cell that gives rise to one or more of the cell type(s) in the epidermis.

label: posterior region of prepharyngeal fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment derived from two prepharyngeal amputations, removing the head and posterior regions of the animal.

label: neuron associated cell (sensu Nematoda and Protostomia)
definition: Cells that are in close proximity to neurons.

label: basal surface of the epidermis
definition: The basal surface of the epidermis in direct contact with the basal lamina.

label: lateral branch
definition: Nerve branches that extend from the lateral side of each cephalic ganglia lobe. Each lobe has nine lateral branches which terminate in sensory organs. Evidence suggests they play a role in chemosensation.

label: metaphase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: ovarian somatic gonadal cell
definition: ophis+ somatic cells (gh4-, nanos-) in the ovary that may provide trophic support to female germline stem cells and differentiating oogonia.

label: nerve
definition: An enclosed, cable-like bundle of axons in the peripheral nervous system originating in a nerve root in the central nervous system (or a condensed nervous structure) connecting with peripheral structures.

label: G2 phase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: pachytene stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing pachytene

label: rhabdite
definition: Straight or curved rod-like structures within the epidermal cells, oriented with long axis at right angles to the epidermal surface, that are discharged into mucous secretions.

label: whole organism
definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of Schmidtea mediterranea or any other flatworm of the class Turbellaria.

label: neuron
definition: The basic cellular unit of nervous tissue. Each neuron consists of a body, an axon, and dendrites. Their purpose is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

label: eye primordium
definition: This primordium develops into eye

label: G1 phase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: spermatogonium
definition: An euploid male germ cell of an early stage of spermatogenesis. In planaria, the gh4+ stem cell daughter exiting the niche undergoes three rounds of transit amplifying division with incomplete cytokinesis prior to transitioning to terminal differentiation.

label: synaptic cleft
definition: The narrow gap that separates the presynaptic and postsynaptic membranes, into which neurotransmitter is released.

label: optic chiasm
definition: A decussation of the diencephalon where the fibers of the optic nerve cross

label: inner longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Inner most body wall muscle fibers arrayed along the anteroposterior axis. These fibers are thicker than the outer longitudinal muscle fibers. The pattern of these muscles differs along the dorsoventral axis, with the dorsal arrangement converging at the central zone of the anterior pole. The ventral arrangement is more parallel or may diverge slightly as it approaches the ventral pole.

label: neuropil
definition: A cluster of neurites that is part of a nervous system and forms a network of dendrites and axons where synapses are present and in which neuronal somata do not occur.

label: cilated neuron
definition: A neuron that has cilia.

label: protonephridial progenitor cell
definition: Neoblasts and post-mitotic, differentiating daughters coexpressing POU2-3, six1/2-2, Sal1, Eya and Osr,required for maintenance and regeneration of protonephridial cell types.

label: serotonergic neural progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, lhx1/5-1+, pitx+ progenitor neoblasts required for specification of tph+ serotonergic neurons.

label: anatomical region
definition: A subdivision of an anatomical compartment.

label: perturbation
definition: An event or occurrence that causes damage to a tissue or organ.

label: dorsal region of lateral fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to or along any edge, which overlaps the lateral region, dorso-lateral region, ventro-lateral region, antero-lateral margin, lateral margin, ventro-lateral margin, postero-lateral margin, dorso-lateral margin, antero-lateral region, postero-lateral region.

label: pharynx
definition: A plicate and protrusible organ that is the sole point of entry and exit for the Triclad gut. It contains epithelial, muscular, secretory and neuronal cell types.

label: ventral region of posterior fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the posterior region of the animal.

label: flame bulb
definition: Terminal structure of protonephridia unit; consists of flame cells.

label: testis somatic gonadal cell progenitor cell
definition: This progenitor cell develops into testis somatic gonadal cell

label: flame cell lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the flame cell

label: Category 5 cell
definition: Post-mitotic, ciliated epidermal cells.

label: cement gland
definition: Glands surrounding the genital atrium that are required for production of the proteinaceous egg capsule shell and stalk.

label: pharynx inner circular muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fiber that runs circumferentially about the pharynx and lies just beneath the inner logitudinal pharynx muscle fibers.

label: pharynx primordium
definition: This primordium develops into pharynx

label: gamma neoblast
definition: An abundant neoblast subclass, exhibiting enriched expression of gata456a, hnf4, prox-1 and nkx2.2, implicated in maintenance and regeneration of the definitive gut.

label: adhesion gland cell
definition: cell which is part of the adhesion gland

label: trail cell
definition: Ovo+ neoblasts and post-mitotic eye progenitors that simultaneously migrate and differentiate into photoreceptor neurons and non-neuronal pigment cup cells comprising the optic cup.

label: lysosome
definition: The digestive component of the cell. They are homogenous, dense, membrane bound organelles filled with acid hydrolases which break down polymers.

label: reproductive structure
definition: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.

label: trunk fragment
definition: A fragment derived from pre- and post-pharyngeal amputations, encompassing the pharynx and parapharyngeal region.

label: plasma membrane part
definition: Any constituent part of the plasma membrane, the membrane surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins.

label: penis papilla
definition: A rounded protuberance, connected to the seminal vesicles, responsible for transferring semen into a mating partner's bursal canal.

label: organ
definition: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions.

label: Category 4 cell
definition: Post-mitotic, mesenchymally and epidermally located progenitors downstream of the Category 3 cells.

label: anchor cell
definition: Specialized epithelial cell located along the dorsoventral margin that surrounds the viscid and releasing gland cells.

label: nuclear outer membrane
definition: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope; continuous with the endoplasmic reticulum of the cell and sometimes studded with ribosomes.

label: chromosome
definition: A structure composed of a very long molecule of DNA and associated proteins (e.g. histones) that carries hereditary information.

label: pharynx inner longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers running anteroposterior which lie beneath both the inner circular muscle fibers and the apical, ciliated portion of the epithium lining the lumenal surface.

label: meiotic prophase II spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic prophase II

label: Stage 2
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 2 - 3 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Sphere formation. A fraction of the blastomeres differentiate into temporary embryonic tissues that provide form and function to the embryo. Undifferentiated blastomeres remain in the embryonic wall.

label: primitive gut
definition: Four large phagocytic cells associated with the embryonic pharynx.

label: rhabdomere
definition: The dendritic process of a bipolar photoreceptor neuron that projects into the optic cup lumen and senses light.

label: pigment granule
definition: A small, subcellular membrane-bounded vesicle containing pigment and/or pigment precursor molecules. Pigment granule biogenesis is poorly understood, as pigment granules are derived from multiple sources including the endoplasmic reticulum, coated vesicles, lysosomes, and endosomes.

label: spermatocyte
definition: A tektin-1+ male germ cell that develops from spermatogonia. The euploid primary spermatocytes undergo meiosis and give rise to the haploid secondary spermatocytes which in turn give rise to spermatids.

label: klf+ sensory neuron progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, klf+ progenitor neoblasts required for production of cintillo+ sensory neurons.

label: anterior region of postpharyngeal fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment derived from two postpharyngeal amputations, removing the anterior region and the tail tip.

label: plasma membrane
definition: The membrane surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins.

label: membrane
definition: A lipid bilayer along with all the proteins and protein complexes embedded in it an attached to it.

label: yolk syncytium
definition: Fused yolk cells surrounding blastomeres undergoing dispersed cleavage during Stages 1 and 2.

label: synaptonemal complex
definition: A proteinaceous scaffold found between homologous chromosomes during meiosis. It consists of 2 lateral elements and a central element, all running parallel to each other. Transverse filaments connect the lateral elements to the central element.

label: embryonic structure
definition: Anatomical structure that is part of an embryo.

label: transverse commissure
definition: Axon tracts from ganglia that cross the midline, connecting the two ventral nerve cords.

label: clonogenic neoblast
definition: Pluripotent piwi-1+ stem cells that self-renew, form expanding colonies and produce differentiating daughters that contribute to multiple organ systems. cNeoblasts are predicted to be broadly distributed across the anteroposterior axis of the adult worm.

label: G1 phase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: intracellular organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, occurring within the cell. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: ventral region of plug fragment
definition: The ventral region of a 3D piece of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: posterior region of lateral fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to or along any edge, which overlaps the lateral region, dorso-lateral region, ventro-lateral region, antero-lateral margin, lateral margin, ventro-lateral margin, postero-lateral margin, dorso-lateral margin, antero-lateral region, postero-lateral region.

label: Category 2 cell
definition: Post-mitotic, mesenchymally located epidermal progenitors downstream of the zeta neoblasts.

label: pharynx outer epithelium surface
definition: Epithelial surface covering the outside of the pharynx.

label: secretory system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts cells and glands devoted to the discharge of substances such as mucus.

label: lateral muscle cell
definition: muscle cell is contained in the lateral region

label: dorsal region of anterior fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the anterior region of the animal.

label: adhesive papilla
definition: Finger-like processes at the terminal pore of adhesive gland cells around the marginal adhesive zone. They protrude past the epidermis and are longer microvilli, and shorter than cilia.

label: commissure
definition: A bundle of nerve fibers crossing from one side to the other side of the brain or spinal cord.

label: vacuole
definition: A closed structure, found only in eukaryotic cells, that is completely surrounded by unit membrane and contains liquid material. Cells contain one or several vacuoles, that may have different functions from each other. Vacuoles have a diverse array of functions. They can act as a storage organelle for nutrients or waste products, as a degradative compartment, as a cost-effective way of increasing cell size, and as a homeostatic regulator controlling both turgor pressure and pH of the cytosol.

label: optic cup
definition: A portion of the eye containing pigment cells and dendritic projections from photoreceptor neurons.

label: peripheral nervous system neuron
definition: Any neuron that is part of a peripheral nervous system.

label: reproductive system product
definition: Products of the reproductive system include gametes, zygotes, yolk cells and egg capsules.

label: anterior muscle cell
definition: muscle cell is contained in the anterior region

label: dorsal region of the whole animal
definition: Three dimensional compartment along the dorsoventral axis that is above the anteroposterior axis, containing the eyes.

label: Stage 1
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development, 0 - 2 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Zygote and dispersed blastomere cleavage in a yolk syncytium.

label: primtive gut cell surface
definition: The surface of the primitive gut cells in contact with the embryonic wall.

label: G2 phase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: heterochromatin
definition: A compact and highly condensed form of chromatin.

label: telophase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic telophase

label: glial cell
definition: A non-neuronal cell of the nervous system. They not only provide physical support, but also respond to injury, regulate the ionic and chemical composition of the extracellular milieu, guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons.

label: quarternary gut branch
definition: Gut branches originating from and connected to the tertiary gut branches.

label: sperm
definition: A mature male germ cell that develops from a spermatid.

label: posterior region of postpharyngeal fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment derived from two postpharyngeal amputations, removing the anterior region and the tail tip.

label: sexual organism
definition: An individual member of the sexual biotype of Schmidtea mediterranea.

label: anterior region of lateral fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to or along any edge, which overlaps the lateral region, dorso-lateral region, ventro-lateral region, antero-lateral margin, lateral margin, ventro-lateral margin, postero-lateral margin, dorso-lateral margin, antero-lateral region, postero-lateral region.

label: embryo
definition: Anatomical entity that comprises the organism in the early stages of growth and differentiation that are characterized by cleavage, the laying down of fundamental tissues, and the formation of primitive organs and organ systems. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

label: regenerating lateral fragment
definition: a lateral fragment that is regenerating

label: posterior region of head fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment derived from a prepharyngeal amputation encompassing the head.

label: anterior photoreceptor neuron
definition: photoreceptor neuron is contained in the anterior region of the eye

label: pharynx radial muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers that run radially, connecting the outer muscle fibers and epithelia with their inner counterparts.

label: telomere
definition: The terminal region of a linear chromosome that includes the telomeric DNA repeats and associated proteins.

label: basophilic gland cell
definition: One of two distinct histochemical classes of gland cells, these are found near the ventral mesenchyme, the pharynx and in the dorsal region of the head. May also be called cyanophilic gland cells.

label: posterior region of plug fragment
definition: The posterior region of a 3D piece of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: testis somatic gonadal cell
definition: dmd-1+ expressing somatic cells within the testis that promote male GSC maintenance. dmd-1+, ophis-1+ somatic gonadal cells ensheath germ cells via long cytoplasmic processes and promote differentiation.

label: chemical wound
definition: An intentional wound produced by non-autonomous chemical means.

label: cytoplasmic vesicle part
definition: Any constituent part of cytoplasmic vesicle, a vesicle formed of membrane or protein, found in the cytoplasm of a cell.

label: smooth endoplasmic reticulum
definition: Endoplamic reticulum that does not contain ribosomes, which synthesizes lipids, phospholipids, and steroids.

label: meiotic G2 phase spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic G2 phase

label: oral hemisphere
definition: Stage 3-5 embryo hemisphere centered around the embryonic pharynx.

label: ganglion
definition: A biological tissue mass of nerve cell bodies.

label: cephalic ganglia primordium
definition: This primordium develops into cephalic ganglia

label: axoneme
definition: The bundle of microtubules and associated proteins that forms the core of cilia (also called flagella) in eukaryotic cells and is responsible for their movements.

label: nucleolus
definition: A small, dense body one or more of which are present in the nucleus of eukaryotic cells. It is rich in RNA and protein, is not bounded by a limiting membrane, and is not seen during mitosis. Its prime function is the transcription of the nucleolar DNA into 45S ribosomal-precursor RNA, the processing of this RNA into 5.8S, 18S, and 28S components of ribosomal RNA, and the association of these components with 5S RNA and proteins synthesized outside the nucleolus. This association results in the formation of ribonucleoprotein precursors; these pass into the cytoplasm and mature into the 40S and 60S subunits of the ribosome.

label: plug fragment
definition: A 3D piece of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: gastrodermis
definition: The single cell layer columnar epithelial lining of the intestine. The gastrodermis is surrounded by a basal lamina and enteric muscle.

label: pharynx nerve plexus
definition: Plexus of nerves located in the pharynx comprised of inner and outer wall rings.

label: pigment cup cell
definition: Non-neuronal, pigmented cells arrayed along the proximal side of the optic cup.

label: postpharyngeal region
definition: Posterior to the pharynx.

label: mouth
definition: The sole point of entry and exit for the Triclad planarian flatworm gut. The mouth is connected to the pharyngeal pouch to allow for exit and re-entry of the pharynx on the ventral side of the animal. The mouth contains several cell types, including epithelial cells, muscle, and secretory cells.

label: thin fragment
definition: A longitudinal fragment lacking a midline and medial structures.

label: ventral region of postpharyngeal fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment derived from two postpharyngeal amputations, removing the anterior region and the tail tip.

label: outer longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed along the anteroposterior axis. Upon regeneration, these muscles are thought to be established from truncated pre-existing fibers.

label: zeta neoblast
definition: An abundant neoblast subclass consisting of p53+, zfp1+ progenitors required for maintenance and regeneration of epidermal cell type(s).

label: cholinergic neuron
definition: Neurons that express choline acetyltransferase.

label: S phase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic S phase

label: euchromatin
definition: A dispersed and relatively uncompacted form of chromatin.

label: parapharyngeal region
definition: Region of the animal lateral to and surrounding the pharynx.

label: G2 phase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: regenerating longitudinal fragment
definition: a longitudinal fragment that is regenerating

label: chromosome arm
definition: Under the microscope chromosomes appear as thin, thread-like structures. They all have a short arm and long arm separated by a primary constriction called the centromere. The short arm is designated as p and the long arm as q.

label: distal tubule
definition: Sinusoidal, non-ciliated tubules connected to proximal tubules within the parenchyma. Tubules are formed via intercellular junctions between two epithelial cells.

label: tertiary gut branch
definition: Gut branches originating from and connected to the secondary gut branches.

label: epidermis
definition: A single cell layer of post-mitotic epithelial cells containing ciliated and non-ciliated cell types forming the exterior surface of the animal.

label: ventral region of longitudinal fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to the midline.

label: testis cell
definition: cell which is part of the testis

label: tail stripe
definition: Medial region of the tail; the parenchymal space between the posterior primary gut branches.

label: pharynx pouch cavity
definition: Anatomical space between the pharynx and the epithelial cells comprising parapharyngeal pouch.

label: serotonergic neuron
definition: Neurons that express the neurotransmitter serotonin.

label: anterior fragment
definition: A fragment encompassing all or part of the anterior region of the animal.

label: photoreceptor neuron
definition: Bipolar photoreceptor neurons with dendritic projections into the optic cup and axons that innervate the underlying brain.

label: gamete
definition: A mature sexual reproductive cell having a single set of unpaired chromosomes.

label: chromatin
definition: The ordered and organized complex of DNA, protein (histones), and sometimes RNA, that forms the chromosome.

label: sperm duct lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by the sperm duct epithelium.

label: germline stem cell
definition: Stem cell that is the precursor of gametes.

label: posterior photoreceptor neuron
definition: photoreceptor neuron is contained in the posterior region of the eye

label: dendrite
definition: A neuron projection that has a short, tapering, morphology. Dendrites receive and integrate signals from other neurons or from sensory stimuli, and conduct nerve impulses towards the axon or the cell body. In most neurons, the impulse is conveyed from dendrites to axon via the cell body, but in some types of unipolar neuron, the impulse does not travel via the cell body.

label: epidermal cell
definition: An epithelial cell of the integument (the outer layer of an organism).

label: eumelanin
definition: The black pigment that gives non-neuronal pigment cells of the optic cup their characteristic color.

label: intercellular junction
definition: A cell junction that forms a connection between two or more cells in a multicellular organism.

label: copulatory region
definition: Portion of the sexual biotype body plan immediately posterior to the parapharyngeal region, and immediately anterior to the tail. Encompasses the copulatory apparatus.

label: neurosecretory neuron
definition: Neuronal cells which synthesize, store and release neurohormones.

label: epidermal rhabdite
definition: Rhabdites located within epidermal cells.

label: wedge wound
definition: A wound resulting from the removal of a piece of tissue from the lateral margin at any given point that extends interiorly to more medial structures.

label: juvenile stage
definition: A postnatal stage of Smed development that initiates with hatching and proceeds until sexual maturity is reached. Reproductive structures develop during the juvenile stage.

label: meiotic telophase I spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic telophase I

label: regenerating fragment
definition: A fragment that has undergone wound healing and is undergoing tissue replacement and morphallaxis.

label: marginal adhesive zone
definition: Zone present along the lateral dorsoventral boundary that sits just underneath the animal, in contact with substrates. It is comprised of bunches of adhesion gland cells whose terminal pores form pore rosettes through the dorsal ventral boundary epidermis.This region of is devoid of rhabdites.

label: guidepost cell
definition: A cell present near the brain and eye where photoreceptor axons form a bundle projecting out from the eye that are near axon choice points. Guidepost cells are  positive for Arrestin, notum, fz5/8-4+, 6G10, and low levels of troponin, tropomyosin, colF-2 and mp-1.

label: ciliated epithelium
definition: Epithelium bearing vibratile cilia on the free surface.

label: embryonic digestive system
definition: A cryptic digestive system in Stage 3-6 embryos comprised of temporary embryonic cell types and organs, including the embryonic pharynx and primitive gut cells. Embryonic gut cells, likely produced from blastomeres, form a phagocytic tissue layer surrounding the inner gut cavity during Stages 4-6. It is not known whether the embryonic gut is temporary embryonic tissue or a definitive tissue. For convenience, the embryonic gut is currently designated as an extraembryonic structure because cell type specific markers for the embryonic gut do not stain the definitive gut in hatchlings or adult animals.

label: stem cell
definition: A relatively undifferentiated cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label: prophase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic prophase

label: parasagittal orientation
definition: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the parasagittal plane, which runs longitudinally, and is never medial.

label: prepharyngeal fragment
definition: A fragment derived from two prepharyngeal amputations, removing the head and posterior regions of the animal.

label: asexual adult
definition: Asexually reproducing Schmidtea mediterranea exist as constitutive adults, undergoing successive cycles of fission and whole animal regeneration. Asexual Schmidtea mediterranea contain primordial germ cells, but do not possess a reproductive system.

label: cell projection
definition: A prolongation or process extending from a cell.

label: female germ cell
definition: Female germ cell is a germ cell that supports female gamete production.

label: ventral region of trunk fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment derived from pre- and post-pharyngeal amputations, encompassing the pharynx and parapharyngeal region.

label: basal lamina of epidermis
definition: Acellular anatomical structure that consists of a thin sheet of fibrous proteins that underlie and support the cells of an epithelium. It separates the cells of an epithelium from any underlying tissue.

label: G2 phase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: afferent neuron
definition: A neuron which conveys sensory information centrally from the periphery.

label: wound
definition: An injury that breaches the epidermis.

label: anatomical system
definition: Multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function.

label: ovary
definition: A gonad containing female germline stem cells which fuel oocyte production. Two ovaries are located ventally, underneath the body wall musculature, immediately posterior to the cephalic ganglia (brain) and adjacent to the ventral nerve cords. The neoblast compartment, including piwi-1+, nanos+ primordial germ cells, fuel formation of the ovaries during juvenile development.

label: pax3/7+ neural progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, pax3/7+ progenitor neoblasts implicated in the production of DBH+ ventral midline neurons.

label: actin-based cell projection
definition: A cell projection supported by an assembly of actin filaments.

label: efferent neuron
definition: A neuron which sends impulses peripherally to activate muscles or secretory cells.

label: cilium
definition: A specialized eukaryotic organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface and of some cytoplasmic parts. Each cilium is largely bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic (plasma) membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored to a basal body. The longitudinal array of microtubules are almost always in a 9+2 array with 2 microtubles in the central cilia bundle and 9 sets of doublet microtubules around the perimeter. The exception to this arrangement is spermatazoa flagella, which have a 9+1 array in planarians.

label: TrpA+ neural progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, runt-1+, ap2+ progenitor neoblasts required for production of TrpA+ neurons.

label: nu neoblast
definition: A population of piwi-2+, ston-2+, elav-2+, ptprd-9+ and msi-1+ progenitors that give rise to one or more neuronal (pc-2+, synapsin+) lineages.

label: Stage 4
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 3 - 5 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Dispersed blastomere cleavage in the embryonic wall. Yolk ingestion into the gut cavity. Early embryonic gut formation.

label: cell body
definition: The portion of a cell bearing surface projections such as axons, dendrites, cilia, or flagella that includes the nucleus, but excludes all cell projections.

label: anterior region of the eye
definition: The anterior region of the eye.

label: Xins cell
definition: A sorted cell population of irradiation-insensitive cells that contains a variety of post-mitotic, differentiated cell types.

label: NBC cell
definition: Guidepost cell present at the medial brain, ventral to the optic chiasm. Closely associated with photoreceptor axons during regneration. Name acronym stands for notum+ brain cells.

label: plug wound
definition: A wound resulting from the removal of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: prophase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic prophase

label: autonomic neuron
definition: A neruon whose cell body is within an autonomic ganglion.

label: visceral musculature
definition: Musculature surrounding internal organs of the body.

label: Stage 3
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 2 - 4 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Dispersed blastomere cleavage in the embryonic wall of nascent spheres. Yolk ingestion into the gut cavity.

label: wedge amputation
definition: A wound resulting from a piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: dorsal region of posterior fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the posterior region of the animal.

label: eye cell
definition: cell which is part of the eye

label: pharynx inner nerve plexus
definition: Ring of the pharynx nerve plexus that is proximal to the lumen.

label: chromosomal_structural_element
definition: structural element of a chromosome, for example, a telomere and a centromere

label: extracellular space
definition: That part of a multicellular organism outside the cells proper, usually taken to be outside the plasma membranes, and occupied by fluid.

label: tail region
definition: Caudal region, beginning at the mouth and ending at posterior pole.

label: sperm duct
definition: A network of tubes that transport sperm from the testes to the seminal vesicles. Tubes connect each testis to ducts that run along the ventral nerve cords. The ducts bifurcate immediately posterior to the pharynx, where they connect to the seminal vesicles.

label: embryonic pharynx circular muscle cell
definition: Differentiated muscle cell present in a circular muscle fiber of the embryonic pharynx.

label: gastrodermis surface
definition: The surface of the gastrodermis in contact with the gut lumen.

label: non-membrane-bounded organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, not bounded by a lipid bilayer membrane. Includes ribosomes, the cytoskeleton and chromosomes.

label: neurite
definition: Cell appendage of the neuron which includes the axon and the dendrite.

label: adenal rhabdite
definition: Rhabdites that are located basally to the epidermis, in the mesenchyme. In Smed these are present in cells likely on their way to becoming part of the mature epidermis.

label: zygotene stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing zygotene

label: presynaptic terminal
definition: Terminal inflated portion of the axon, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label: primary gut branch
definition: The largest branch of the triclad intestine. It is comprised of the gastrodermis, a columnar epithelium, surrounded by basal lamina and visceral musculature.

label: dorsal ventral margin of the whole animal
definition: Region along the edge of the animal where the dorsal and ventral surfaces meet.

label: prophase  oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic prophase

label: non-ciliated neuron
definition: A neuron cell that does not have cilia.

label: NMC cell
definition: Guidepost cell assocaited with the visual circuit, present at the axon choice point ventral, posterior to and slightly medial to the eye.  Name acronym stands for notum+ muscle cells at the choice point.

label: embryonic pharynx lumen
definition: A lumen enclosed by the embryonic pharynx epithelial cells through which yolk cells are transported into the embryonic gut cavity.

label: male primordial germ cell
definition: Cells coexpressing piwi-1 and nanos that are required for male gonad formation. Primordial germ cells are present in both asexual adults and sexual hermaphrodites. This term may be redundant with spermatogonial stem cell.

label: lateral region of the whole animal
definition: The lateral region of the medio-lateral axis of the whole animal.

label: pharynx outer epidermal cell
definition: Heavily ciliated, insunk epithelial cells bounding the outside of the pharynx. Outer pharynx epithelial cell nuclei are positioned beneath the pharynx musculature.

label: cintillo+ sensory neuron
definition: A subset of sensory neurons located along the dorsal head margin.

label: anterior region of trunk fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment derived from pre- and post-pharyngeal amputations, encompassing the pharynx and parapharyngeal region.

label: yolk cell
definition: An extraembryonic cell, produced by somatic vitellogenic glands in adult hermaphrodites, that provides nutrition to the developing embryo.

label: Hyman vesicle
definition: PROG-2-5 positive granules that range in size from 0.5um to 1um present in epithelia and epithelia progenitor cells. These are distinct from rhabdites.

label: interneuron
definition: Most generally any neuron which is not motor or sensory. Interneurons may also refer to neurons whose axons remain within a particular brain region as contrasted with projection neurons which have axons projecting to other brain regions.

label: S phase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic S phase

label: FACS sorted cell population
definition: Any number of cells from dissociated planarian tissue sorted via a FACS sorter for any parameter.

label: G1 phase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: esophagus
definition: Attachment between the triclad gut and the proximal end of the pharynx.

label: cephalic ganglia progenitor cell
definition: A progenitor cell that gives rise to one or more of the cell type(s) in the nervous system.

label: fission
definition: A form of asexual reproduction resulting in self-amputation of posterior tissue, generating an anterior fragment and a fission fragment.

label: posterior region of anterior fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the anterior region of the animal.

label: metaphase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: goblet cell
definition: Secretory cells that release digestive enzymes into the lumen of the intestine.

label: unipolar neuron
definition: Neuron with one neurite that extends from the cell body.

label: lateral nerve
definition: A nerve extending laterally from the ventral nerve cord that innervates the submuscular plexus.

label: posterior region of trunk fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment derived from pre- and post-pharyngeal amputations, encompassing the pharynx and parapharyngeal region.

label: ventral nerve cord
definition: The pair of closely united ventral longitudinal nerves with their segmental ganglia that is characteristic of many elongate invertebrates (as earthworms)[BTO]. A large process bundle that runs along the vental mid-line extending from the ventral region of the nerve ring[WB]. The ventral cord is one of the distinguishing traits of the central nervous system of all arthropods (such as insects, crustaceans and arachnids) as well as many other invertebrates, such as the annelid worms[GO].

label: anterior region of tail fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment derived from a postpharyngeal amputation encompassing the tail.

label: sensory cell
definition: A cell that performs a sensory function.

label: tissue
definition: Multicellular anatomical structure that consists of many cells of one or a few types, arranged in an extracellular matrix such that their long-range organisation is at least partly a repetition of their short-range organisation.

label: renal system
definition: The renal system is an anatomical system that maintains fluid balance and contributes to electrolyte balance, acid/base balance, and disposal of nitrogenous waste products.

label: secretory pore
definition: The opening by which the gland cells secrete mucus to the exterior of the animal.

label: head region
definition: The head is the anterior-most division of the body [GO]. A three dimensional compartment bounded by the anterior margin or the head and the posterior boundary of the cephalic ganglia (brain).

label: protonephridial lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the protonephridia

label: cell junction
definition: A cellular component that forms a specialized region of connection between two or more cells or between a cell and the extracellular matrix. At a cell junction, anchoring proteins extend through the plasma membrane to link cytoskeletal proteins in one cell to cytoskeletal proteins in neighboring cells or to proteins in the extracellular matrix.

label: sensory neuron
definition: Any neuron having a sensory function; an afferent neuron conveying sensory impulses.

label: point incision
definition: A breach of the epidermis made with a sharp pointed object, like a needle or an insect pin.

label: sperm duct epithelial cell
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells comprising the sperm ducts.

label: Stage 6
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 7 - 9 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis and morphogenesis. Definitive organ formation. Temporary embryonic cell types degenerate. Embryo elongation.

label: visual system
definition: The sensory system subserving the sense of vision.

label: oviduct epithelium
definition: Ciliated epithelium lining the oviduct.

label: Category 3 cell
definition: Post-mitotic, mesenchymally located epidermal progenitors downstream of the Category 2 cells.

label: reproductive system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with reproduction.

label: gonad primoridium
definition: This primordium develops into gonad

label: pharynx pouch
definition: An epithelial structure housing the pharynx, connected to the esophagus and mouth.

label: neuropeptidergic neuron
definition: A neuron that produces and releases neuropeptides at chemical synapses.

label: gap junction
definition: A cell-cell junction composed of pannexins or innexins and connexins, two different families of channel-forming proteins.

label: Smed asexual biotype
definition: Asexual animal strains that reproduce solely through fission followed by whole body regeneration. Asexual Smed are stable diploids that harbor a chromosome translocation, making them karyotypically distinct from sexual Smed.

label: nuclear pore
definition: Any of the numerous similar discrete openings in the nuclear envelope of a eukaryotic cell, where the inner and outer nuclear membranes are joined.

label: anaphase spermatogonia
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: nucleus
definition: A membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated. In most cells, the nucleus contains all of the cell's chromosomes except the organellar chromosomes, and is the site of RNA synthesis and processing. In some species, or in specialized cell types, RNA metabolism or DNA replication may be absent.

label: fission plane
definition: Transverse anatomical plane, located approximately 1-2 mm from the posterior extremity of an adult animal, at which fission occurs.

label: anterior pole cell
definition: cell which is part of the anterior pole

label: post-blastema region
definition: Adjacent to blastema, or proximal to blastema.

label: cephalic ganglia lobe
definition: One of two bilaterally symmetric structures comprising the planarian brain.

label: posterior region of longitudinal fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to the midline.

label: octopaminergic neuron
definition: Neurons that express the biogenic amine octopamine.

label: secretory granule
definition: A small subcellular vesicle, surrounded by a membrane, that is formed from the Golgi apparatus and contains a highly concentrated protein destined for secretion. Secretory granules move towards the periphery of the cell and upon stimulation, their membranes fuse with the cell membrane, and their protein load is exteriorized. Processing of the contained protein may take place in secretory granules.

label: anterior commissure
definition: A bundle of nerve fibers connecting the two cephalic ganglia.

label: wedge fragment
definition: A piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: distal tubule epithelial cell
definition: Nonciliated epithelial cells that assemble into protonephridial distal tubules.

label: X1(FS) cell
definition: A heterogeneous sorted cell population of unstained planarian cells with similar size and complexity to irradiation-sensitive, cycling cells contained in the X1 gate. Unlike X1 cells, X1(FS) cells are amenable to cell transplantation.

label: pharynx inner epidermal cell
definition: Epithelial cells lining the inside of the pharynx. In Smed, distally located cells are heavily ciliated.

label: G2 phase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: juvenile organism
definition: A sexually immature member of the Schmidtea mediterranea sexuallly reproducing biotype

label: cytoplasmic part
definition: Any constituent part of the cytoplasm, all of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures.

label: meiotic telophase II spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic telophase II

label: anterior gut branch
definition: A branch of the triclad gut located anterior to the pharynx.

label: meiosis II stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiosis II cell cycle phase

label: anterior region of longitudinal fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to the midline.

label: pigment cell
definition: A pigment cell is a cell that contains pigment granules.

label: dorsal region of longitudinal fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to the midline.

label: commissural neuron
definition: A neuron that has an axon which crosses the midline.

label: gland cell
definition: Specialized insunk epithelial cells located in the mesenchyme that participate in mucus secretion. They are characterized by elongated cell bodies with long cytoplasmic projections that terminate between, or penetrate directly throughepithelial cells and form a secretory pore at the surface.

label: pharynx neuron
definition: neuron which is part of the pharynx

label: bursal canal
definition: The passageway connecting the genital atrium to the copulatory bursa. Part of the copulatory apparatus. During mating, sperm from a partner is deposited into the bursal canal, where it collects in the copulatory bursa before travelling up the oviducts to the tuba.

label: electrically responsive cell
definition: A cell whose function is determined by its response to an electric signal.

label: embryonic subdivision
definition: Anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole developing/ embryonic organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems.

label: anterior region of head fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment derived from a prepharyngeal amputation encompassing the head.

label: derived cell population
definition: Cells isolated from dissociated planarian tissue.

label: oviduct epithelial cell
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells that assemble into the oviduct.

label: pigment cup primordium
definition: This primordium develops into optic cup

label: head margin
definition: Peripheral region of the head.

label: muscle progenitor cell
definition: Progenitor neoblasts implicated in the maintenance and regeneration of muscle fibers.

label: S phase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic S phase

label: non-ciliated epidermis
definition: Differentiating, immature epidermal cells lacking cilia.

label: presynaptic vesicle
definition: A secretory organelle, typically 50 nm in diameter, of presynaptic nerve terminals; accumulates in high concentrations of neurotransmitters and secretes these into the synaptic cleft by fusion with the 'active zone' of the presynaptic plasma membrane.

label: ventral epidermis
definition: Single cell layer of ventral, post-mitotic, heavily ciliated epithelial cells

label: pore
definition: An anatomical space that is an opening, usually at the end of a canal or duct, on the surface of the integument or the lining of an internal anatomical space.

label: regenerating trunk fragment
definition: a trunk fragment that is regenerating

label: NME cell
definition: Guidepost cell associated with the visual circuit that are present near the eye, located along axons just anterior and ventral to the eye. Name acronym stands for notum+ muscle cell near eye.

label: pharynx outer circular muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers thar run circumferentially about the pharynx and lie just beneath the outer longitudinal pharynx muscles.

label: specialized neoblast
definition: A presumptive progenitor cell that expresses both pan-neoblast markers and pro-differentiation gene(s), frequently developmental transcription factors, implicated in lineage commitment and tissue-specific differentiation programs.

label: parenchymal musculature
definition: Muscles that are present through the mesenchyme, inclusing dorsal-ventral muscles, intestinal muscles and pharynx muscles.

label: G1 phase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: diplotene stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing diplotene

label: lateral fragment
definition: A fragment derived from an amputation parallel to or along any edge, which overlaps the lateral region, dorso-lateral region, ventro-lateral region, antero-lateral margin, lateral margin, ventro-lateral margin, postero-lateral margin, dorso-lateral margin, antero-lateral region, postero-lateral region. [SMR: a fragment that encompasses the side of the animal, not necessarily longituduinal, or parallel to the midline]

label: circular muscle progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, nkx1-1+ progenitor neoblasts required for specification of circular muscle fibers.

label: prophase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic prophase

label: S phase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic S phase

label: posterior region of wedge fragment
definition: The posterior region of a piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: aboral hemisphere
definition: Stage 3-5 embryo hemisphere centered around the pole opposite the embryonic pharynx.

label: oviduct
definition: Ciliated tubes adjacent to the ventral nerve cords, adjoining the tuba and the bursal canal, that transport fertilized oocytes to the genital atrium.

label: obsolete pharynx nerve plexus
definition: Plexus of nerves located in the pharynx comprised of inner and outer wall rings.

label: oral opening
definition: The orifice that connects the mouth to the exterior of the body.

label: reproductive organ
definition: An organ involved in reproduction

label: seminal vesicle
definition: Glandular pouches adjoining the sperm ducts which produce seminal fluid.

label: auricle
definition: A sense organ located along the dorsolateral head margin. The auricular groove is highly innervtated by ciliated sensory neurons, and has an altered epidermis devoid of rhabdites and gland cells.

label: testis nerve plexus
definition: Nerve plexus surrounding the testis.

label: gonopore
definition: The gonopore, a component of the copulatory apparatus, is an opening located on the ventral side of the animal posterior to the pharynx. The gonopore is the sole point of exit and entry for the reproductive system, allowing from reciprocal exchange of sperm during copulation and egg capsule laying.

label: enteric musculature
definition: Visceral muscle surrounding the gut.

label: posterior fragment
definition: A fragment encompassing all or part of the posterior region of the animal.

label: anterior primary gut branch
definition: The single, central gut branch of the triclad gut anterior to the pharynx.

label: multicellular anatomical structure
definition: An anatomical structure that has more than one cell as a part.

label: dorsal epidermis progenitor cell
definition: A progenitor cell that gives rise to one or more of the cell type(s) in the dorsal epidermis.

label: primitive ectoderm surface
definition: The apical surface of the single layered primitive ectoderm that is in contact with the environment.

label: motor neuron
definition: An efferent neuron that passes from the central nervous system or a ganglion toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes or inhibits movement.

label: ciliated epithelial cell
definition: An epithelial cell that has cilia.

label: adhesion gland
definition: Groupings of specialized epithelial cells located along the dorsal ventral margin. Adhesion glands are comprised of three cell types, the viscid and releasing gland cells which penetrate through an epithelial anchor cell and terminate at the epidermal surface.

label: viscid gland cell
definition: A specialized insunk epithelial cell that is part of the adhesion glands which is responsible for production and excretion of the viscid substance allowing adherence to a substrate.

label: sensory system
definition: Anatomical system that overlaps the nervous system and is responsible for receiving and processing sensory information.

label: epidermal progenitor cell
definition: Mitotically active zeta neoblasts and their post-mitotic descendants which undergo progressive differentiation and outward directed movement through the mesenchyme prior to incorporation into the epidermis, where terminal differentiation occurs.

label: pharynx inner epithelium surface
definition: The epithelial surface lining the interior of the pharynx, facing the lumen.

label: longitudinal fragment
definition: a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to the midline.

label: spermatogonial stem cell
definition: gh4+, nanos+ cells residing at the testis periphery that self-renew and give rise to differentiating daughters that will ultimately produce haploid sperm.

label: proximal-distal axis of the whole animal
definition: Axis that starts at the distal part of an appendage, closest to the body, and runs to the proximal part of an appendage, farthest from the body.

label: progenitor cell
definition: A cycling neoblast and/or post-mitotic cell that is primed or irreversibly committed to a tissue-specific differentation program

label: oocyte
definition: A female germ cell that has entered meiosis.

label: chemical amputation
definition: Amputation carried out by application of chemicals.

label: blastema
definition: A regenerating tissue composed of a proliferative mass of undifferentiated progenitor cells from which new differentiated structures arise.

label: embryonic gut cell
definition: Dispersed, phagocytic gut cells that appear during Stage 4 and ultimately generate a honeycomb-like lattice surrounding the central gut cavity in Stage 5 embryos. Early embryonic gut cell specific transcripts are expressed from Stage 4-6, and are downregulated during Stage 7.

label: S phase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic S phase

label: early male germ cell
definition: A premeiotic male germ cell (i.e., a spermatogonial stem cell or transit amplifying spermatogonial cell).

label: G1 phase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: genital atrium
definition: A chamber where egg capsules are formed. One or more zygotes and yolk cells produced by the vitelline glands collect in the genital atrium; glands surrounding the genital atrium produce the egg capsule shell.

label: left-right axis of the whole animal
definition: Axis perpendicular to both the anteroposterior and dorsoventral axis that runs from the left side of the animal, through the medial region (center) and out to the right side.

label: dorsal-ventral muscle cell
definition: A muscle cell that runs in the transverse plane that connects the dorsal and ventral sides of the animal.

label: mechanoreceptor cell
definition: A cell specialized to transduce mechanical stimuli and relay that information centrally in the nervous system.

label: digestive system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs devoted to the ingestion, digestion, and assimilation of food and the discharge of residual wastes.

label: sperm duct epithelial surface
definition: Epithelial surface lining the sperm duct.

label: meiotic prophase I spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic prophase I

label: ventral region of tail fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment derived from a postpharyngeal amputation encompassing the tail.

label: pharynx epithelium
definition: Epithelia associated with the pharynx organ.

label: anaphase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: tail blastema
definition: blastema which develops into tail region

label: Smed sexual biotype
definition: Strains of cross-fertilizing hemaphrodites that reproduce sexually and do not undergo fission. After mating, each parent lays an egg capsule containing one or more embryos. Sexual Smed are stable diploids.

label: tail fragment
definition: A fragment derived from a postpharyngeal amputation encompassing the tail.

label: extraembryonic structure
definition: A multicellular anatomical structure that is associated with an embryo and derived from the zygote from which it develops, but which does not contribute to the embryo proper or to structures that are part of the same organism after embryogenesis.

label: posterior region of the eye
definition: The posterior region of the eye.

label: embryonic cell
definition: A cell of the embryo.

label: pharynx outer epithelium
definition: Heavily ciliated epidermal cells covering the outer surface of the pharynx shaft. These are "insunk" epidermal cells in which the nuclei reside behind the layers of longitudinal and circumferential muscles and the epithelial cell body sends out a ciliated projection to the surface to cover and encase the shaft.

label: enteric neuron
definition: A neruon contained within with the enteric nervous system (gastrodermal plexus).

label: adherens junction
definition: A cell junction at which anchoring proteins (cadherins or integrins) extend through the plasma membrane and are attached to actin filaments.

label: melanosome
definition: A tissue-specific, membrane-bounded cytoplasmic organelle within which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored. Melanosomes are synthesized in melanocyte cells.

label: fragment
definition: A piece of tissue isolated from the body.

label: ventral region of anterior fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the anterior region of the animal.

label: melanin pigment granule
definition: pigment granule which is part of the eumelanin

label: secretory duct
definition: A tubular structure that transports secreted or excreted substances.

label: primordium
definition: Primordia are populations of contiguous cells that are morphologically distinct and already correspond in extent to a later organ/tissue.

label: G1 phase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: protonephridia
definition: Excretory organs consisting of flame cells, proximal tubules, and distal tubules connected to a mesenchymal collecting duct.

label: embryonic pharynx epithelial cell
definition: foxA1+ epithelial cell contained in the embryonic pharynx.

label: dorsal-ventral axis of the whole animal
definition: Axis that runs along the short axis of the animal, perpendicular to the anteroposterior axis, running from the dorsal (back) side of the animal to the ventral (belly) side of the animal. This axis splits anterior and posterior regions of the animal to either side.

label: flame cell
definition: Terminal structure of the protonephridia unit, capping the proximal tubules. Flame cells are defined by the filtration weir‚ or filtration diaphragm, which consists of closely apposed strands of cytoplasm surrounding a central cilia bundle, and by numerous microvilli between weir and cilia. Positive for acetyated tubulin.

label: dorsal region of prepharyngeal fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment derived from two prepharyngeal amputations, removing the head and posterior regions of the animal.

label: microvillus
definition: Thin cylindrical membrane-covered projections on the surface of an animal cell containing a core bundle of actin filaments.

label: central nervous system neuron
definition: Any neuron that is part of a central nervous system.

label: secondary gut branch
definition: Gut branches, originating from and connected to the primary gut branches, that extend laterally towards the body edge.

label: membrane part
definition: Any constituent part of a membrane, a double layer of lipid molecules that encloses all cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins.

label: gastrodermal plexus
definition: A thin net of single nerve fibers located around the gut.

label: enteric muscle cell
definition: cell which is part of the enteric musculature

label: G2 phase  oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: anterior pole progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, foxD+, prep+ progenitor neoblasts required for formation of the anterior pole.

label: cell-cell adhesion
definition: The attachment of one cell to another cell via adhesion molecules.

label: optic cup progenitor cell
definition: A progenitor cell that gives rise to optic cup cells of the eye.

label: dorsal region of tail fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment derived from a postpharyngeal amputation encompassing the tail.

label: medial muscle cell
definition: Subset of dorsal-ventral muscle cells located in the medial body region.

label: pharynx longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers running anteroposterior (proximal to distal).

label: dorsal region of plug fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a 3D piece of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: synaptic vesicle
definition: A secretory organelle, typically 50 nm in diameter, of presynaptic nerve terminals; accumulates in high concentrations of neurotransmitters and secretes these into the synaptic cleft by fusion with the 'active zone' of the presynaptic plasma membrane.

label: ventral region of lateral fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to or along any edge, which overlaps the lateral region, dorso-lateral region, ventro-lateral region, antero-lateral margin, lateral margin, ventro-lateral margin, postero-lateral margin, dorso-lateral margin, antero-lateral region, postero-lateral region.

label: visual system cell
definition: cell which is part of the visual system

label: gut
definition: The planarian triclad gut contains a central anterior gut branch connected to two posterior gut branches arranged around the pharynx. Secondary gut branches extend laterally from the primary gut branches, while tertiary gut branches extend from the secondary branches. Food and waste enter and exit the gut through the pharynx.

label: embryonic wall
definition: The parenchymal space between the gut cavity and the primitive ectoderm containing undifferentiated blastomeres in Stage 3-5 embryos.

label: definitive organism subdivision
definition: Anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole adult or juvenile organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems.

label: stalk
definition: A thin, flexible rod that anchors an egg capsule to a solid substrate.

label: primitive ectoderm
definition: A single cell layer of extraembryonic, post-mitotic ectodermal cells bounding the embryo. The primitive ectoderm forms during Stage 2 and is thought to degenerate as the definitive epidermis forms during Stages 5-7.

label: ovary primordium
definition: This primordium develops into ovary

label: anaphase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: ectolecithal embryo
definition: Turbellarian (freshwater flatworm) embryos that undergo a modified form of cleavage due to separation of oocyte and yolk. Yolk is not contained within oocytes, and is produced by somatic vitellogenic gland cells.

label: biotype
definition: Organisms sharing a specified genotype or karyotype.

label: parenchyma
definition: A loosely organized collection of connective tissue and cells, including neoblasts and their immediate progeny, located in the space outside of the organs between the body wall musculature and the gut.

label: surgical wound
definition: A wound produced by non-autonomous physical means.

label: regenerating head fragment
definition: a head fragment that is regenerating

label: anterior-posterior axis of the whole animal
definition: Axis that runs along the long axis of the animal from anterior (head) to posterior (tail). It is perpendicular to the dorsoventral axis and as such, it splits dorsal and ventral regions of the animal to either side.

label: muscle cell
definition: A mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte. This cell has as part of its cytoplasm myofibrils organized in various patterns.

label: pharynx muscle cell
definition: muscle cell which is part of the pharynx

label: S phase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic S phase

label: pharynx circular muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers running circumferentially about the pharynx.

label: male germ cell
definition: A male germ cell is a germ cell that supports male gamete production.

label: spermatid
definition: A male germ cell that develops from the haploid secondary spermatocytes. Without further division, spermatids undergo structural changes and give rise to spermatozoa.

label: regenerating postpharyngeal fragment
definition: a postpharyngeal fragment that is regenerating

label: oral-aboral axis of the embryo
definition: Axis that runs from the oral pole and to the aboral pole of the spherical embryo (Stage 3 through early Stage 6). The oral pole is centered around the embryonic pharynx; the aboral pole is located opposite the embryonic pharynx.

label: brain visual center
definition: Region of the cephalic ganglia innervated by the optic nerve (posterior-projecting photoreceptor neuron fasiculated axons).

label: electrically signaling cell
definition: A cell that initiates an electrical signal and passes that signal to another cell.

label: thick fragment
definition: A longitudinal fragment containing the preexisting midline and medial structures.

label: glycogen granule
definition: Cytoplasmic bead-like structures of animal cells, visible by electron microscope. Each granule is a functional unit with the biosynthesis and catabolism of glycogen being catalyzed by enzymes bound to the granule surface.

label: sigma neoblast
definition: A heterogeneous subpopulation of neoblasts with enriched expression of SoxP-1 and SoxP-2 thought to contain both pluripotent stem cells and tissue-specific progenitors.

label: body wall muscle cell
definition: cell which is part of the body wall musculature

label: lipid droplet
definition: An intracellular non-membrane-bounded organelle comprising a matrix of coalesced lipids surrounded by a phospholipid monolayer. May include associated proteins.

label: pharynx pouch epithelial cell
definition: epithelial cell which is part of the pharynx pouch

label: bipolar neuron
definition: A type of interneuron that has two neurites, usually an axon and a dendrite, extending from opposite poles of an ovoid cell body.

label: pharynx pouch epithelium
definition: An epithelial monolayer lining the pharynx pouch cavity.

label: female primordial germ cell
definition: Cells expressing nanos that are located ventrally in the location that the ovaries form. Primordial germ cells are present in both asexual adults and sexual hermaphrodites. This term may be redundant with oogonial stem cell.

label: extracellular organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, occurring outside the cell. Includes, for example, extracellular membrane vesicles (EMVs) and the cellulosomes of anaerobic bacteria and fungi.

label: midline
definition: The median line/ plane of bilateral symmetry along the anteroposterior axis.

label: regenerating tail fragment
definition: a tail fragment that is regenerating

label: prepharyngeal region
definition: Region of the juvenile or adult animal between the posterior end of the cephalic ganglia and the anterior end of the pharynx.

label: metaphase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: ER membrane
definition: The lipid bilayer surrounding the endoplasmic reticulum.

label: extracellular matrix
definition: A structure lying external to one or more cells, which provides structural support, biochemical or biomechanical cues for cells or tissues.

label: adult hermaphrodite
definition: A fully formed, sexually mature organism that reproduces through cross-fertilization.

label: metaphase spermatogonia
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: apical surface of the epidermis
definition: The apical surface of the single layered epidermis that is in contact with the environment.

label: sympathetic neuron
definition: Sympathetic neurons are part of the sympathetic nervous system and are primarily adrenergic producing the neurotransmitter noradrenalin along with other neuropeptides.

label: amputation
definition: A wound resulting in two or more separate tissue fragments.

label: mucus
definition: A secreted, mucin-rich extracellular substance coating the epidermal surface of the animal implicated in gliding locomotion, substrate adhesion, innate immunity and predator avoidance.

label: rhabdome
definition: The light sensing structure consisting of photoreceptor neuron dendrites that project into the optic lumen and show close associations with eumelanin-containing pigment cup cells.

label: elongate spermatid
definition: Spermatids expressing protein kinase A undergoing morphogenic changes to make mature sperm.

label: Stage 8
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 13 - 15 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis and organ maturation continues. Hatching.

label: posterior region of tail fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment derived from a postpharyngeal amputation encompassing the tail.

label: basal body
definition: A membrane-tethered, short cylindrical array of microtubules and associated proteins found at the base of a eukaryotic cilium (also called flagellum) that is similar in structure to a centriole and derives from it. The cilium basal body is the site of assembly and remodelling of the cilium and serves as a nucleation site for axoneme growth. As well as anchoring the cilium, it is thought to provide a selective gateway regulating the entry of ciliary proteins and vesicles by intraflagellar transport.

label: head blastema
definition: blastema which develops into head region

label: gonad
definition: Reproductive organ that produces and releases eggs (ovary) or sperm (testis).

label: pharynx pouch epithelial surface
definition: The surface of the parapharyngeal pouch facing the pharynx.

label: regenerating wedge fragment
definition: a wedge fragment that is regenerating

label: head fragment
definition: A fragment derived from a prepharyngeal amputation encompassing the head.

label: secretory cell
definition: A cell that specializes in controlled release of one or more substances.

label: sagittal orientation
definition: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the sagittal plane. This plane runs longitudinally and is not necessarily medial.

label: mitochondrion
definition: A spherical to rod shaped organelle that generates the majority of a cell's supply of ATP via cellular respiration. Mitochondria have their own genome and consist of outer and inner membranes, the latter folds inward to form cristae. This folding increases the surface area of the membrane and thus increases the space available to produce ATP. The inner and outer membranes are separated by an intermembrane space, and the inner membrane encloses the matrix.

label: flagellum
definition: Planarian undulipodia consisting of spermatazoa cell posterior protrusions. Planarian spermatozoa contain two flagella and are composed of 9 + 1 axonemal microtubule arrangements in their flagella (markedly different from the 9 + 2 structures generally observed in sperm of other animals).

label: presynaptic cell
definition: The part of a synapse that is part of the presynaptic cell.

label: anaphase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: Stage 7
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 9 - 11 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis and organ maturation continues. Embryos elongated. Eyes just visible. Onset of gliding motility.

label: egg capsule
definition: A proteinaceous, semi-permeable shell housing yolk cells and one or more embryos.Egg capsules are anchored to a substrate via a stalk.

label: ventral region of wedge fragment
definition: The ventral region of a piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: telophase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic telophase

label: intracellular non-membrane-bounded organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, not bounded by a lipid bilayer membrane and occurring within the cell. Includes ribosomes, the cytoskeleton and chromosomes

label: dorsal midline
definition: The median line/plane of bilateral symmetry along the anteroposterior axis on the dorsal surface of the animal.

label: dorsal region of postpharyngeal fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment derived from two postpharyngeal amputations, removing the anterior region and the tail tip.

label: anterior region of prepharyngeal fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment derived from two prepharyngeal amputations, removing the head and posterior regions of the animal.

label: round spermatid
definition: A cyst of 8 interconnected spermatocytes undergoes meiosis, producing 32 haploid round spermatids. Round spermatids express protein kinase A, andundergo morphogenesis to produce mature sperm.

label: excitatory motor neuron
definition: A motor neuron that is capable of directly inducing muscle contraction.

label: excretory cell
definition: A cell involved in the elimination of metabolic and foreign toxins, and in maintaining the ionic, acid-base and water balance of biological fluids.

label: tuba lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by tuba. Oocyte(s) are fertilized in the tuba lumen by sperm that traveled up the oviduct.

label: telophase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic telophase

label: incision
definition: A surgical cut that breaches the epidermis, made with a defined edge.

label: pharynx outer longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers running anteroposterior which lie just underneath the apical, cilaited portion of the outer epithelium.

label: prepharyngeal cell
definition: cell which is part of the prepharyngeal region

label: oogonial stem cell
definition: A piwi-1+, nanos+ cell residing in the ovary that self-renews and give rise to oogonial cells that differentiate into oocytes.

label: proximal tubule
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells form tubules, generating coiled, branching units terminating in flame bulbs. Tubules are formed via intercellular junctions between two epithelial cells. Proximal tubules are connected to non-ciliated distal tubules within the parenchyma.

label: tail tip
definition: The posterior-medial region of the tail margin.

label: circular muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed around the dorsoventral axis. Upon regeneration, these are thought to be produced de novo in the blastema.

label: copulatory bursa
definition: An organ that receives and stores sperm from mating partners.

label: embryonic pharynx
definition: An innervated, muscular pump that ingests yolk cells into the gut cavity. The embryonic pharynx is an extraembryonic tissue that forms during Stage 2, functions during Stages 3-5, and degenerates during Stages 6-7.

label: axon tract
