definition: A group of axons linking two or more neuropils and having a common origin, termination

label: bulbar cavity
definition: An enlarged portion of the seminal vesicle, comprised of secretory epithelial cells, that connects to the ejaculatory duct within the penis papilla.

label: gastrodermal cell
definition: cell which is part of the gastrodermis

label: premeiotic germ cell
definition: A diploid germline stem cell or transit amplifying germ cell that has not committed to undergoing meiotic DNA replication, reductive divisions or terminal differentiation.

label: testis primordium
definition: This primordium develops into testis

label: telophase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic telophase

label: nervous system
definition: The nervous system is an organ system containing predominantly neuron and glial cells. In bilaterally symmetrical organisms, it is arranged in a network of tree-like structures connected to a central body. The main functions of the nervous system are to regulate and control body functions, and to receive sensory input, process this information, and generate behavior [CUMBO].

label: proximal tubule epithelial cell
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells that assemble into proximal tubules.

label: post-meiotic germ cell
definition: A haploid gamete undergoing terminal differentiation.

label: dorsal region of head fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a fragment derived from a prepharyngeal amputation encompassing the head.

label: mechanosensory neuron
definition: Any neuron that is capable of some detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception.

label: regenerating plug fragment
definition: a plug fragment that is regenerating

label: regeneration
definition: The regrowth of a lost or destroyed body part, such as an organ or tissue. This process may occur via renewal, repair, and/or growth alone (i.e. increase in size or mass).

label: cut
definition: A wound or cleft resulted from tissue separation into parts or laid open or penetrated with a sharp edge or instrument.

label: plug amputation
definition: A wound resulting from an amputation of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: copulatory apparatus
definition: Accessory reproductive structures involved in copulation, egg capsule development and laying.

label: endoplasmic reticulum
definition: Network of interconnected, flattened, and/or tubular membrane, known as cisternae. This membrane is contiguous with the outer nuclear membrane. The endoplasmic reticulum is involved in both protein and lipid synthesis.

label: glutamatergic neuron
definition: Neurons that express the biogenic amine glutamate.

label: anterior tip
definition: The anterior-medial region of the head margin.

label: intracellular part
definition: Any constituent part of the living contents of a cell; the matter contained within (but not including) the plasma membrane, usually taken to exclude large vacuoles and masses of secretory or ingested material. In eukaryotes it includes the nucleus and cytoplasm.

label: collecting duct epithelial cell
definition: Nonciliated epithelial cells that assemble into collecting ducts.

label: bounding membrane of organelle
definition: Examples include the outer membranes of double membrane bound organelles such as mitochondria as well as the bounding membranes of single-membrane bound organelles such as lysosomes.

label: blastomere
definition: An undifferentiated, cycling embryonic cell in Stage 1-5 embryos that expresses piwi-1, numerous adult asexual neoblast enriched genes, and early embryo enriched genes. Blastomeres give rise to temporary embryonic tissues during Stage 2, continue dividing asynchronously in the embryonic wall, and ultimately give rise to neoblasts and adult lineage progenitors beginning in Stage 5.

label: telophase  oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic telophase

label: primitive ectoderm cell
definition: Primitive ectoderm cells differentiate from the blastomere population, exit the cell cycle and interact to boud the embryo during Stage 2.

label: postpharyngeal fragment
definition: A fragment derived from two postpharyngeal amputations, removing the anterior region and the tail tip.

label: intracellular granule
definition: Cytoplasmic part which forms a distinctive granular particle, which may or may not be visible using light microscopy.

label: meiotic S phase spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic S phase

label: gut branch
definition: The triclad planarian gut is serially bifrucated into connected lumens where each bifrucation is a branch.

label: anterior region of wedge fragment
definition: The anterior region of a piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: ventral region of head fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment derived from a prepharyngeal amputation encompassing the head.

label: Category 1 cell
definition: Irradiation-sensitive, mesenchymal cells that are absent from the head region anterior to the eyes and the pharynx. The Category 1 designation encompasses the neoblast population.

label: dorsal region of the epidermis
definition: Single cell layer of dorsal, post-mitotic, epithelial cells containing the dorsal stripe.

label: pharynx musculature
definition: The total musculature within the pharynx.

label: inner zone of gland cells
definition: Gland or secretory cells sandwiched between muscle and epidermal layers in the pharynx.

label: lumen
definition: The cavity or channel within a tube or tubular organ such as a blood vessel or the intestine.

label: subepidermal nerve plexus
definition: Plexus of nerves located just between the epidermis and the body wall musculature.

label: leptotene stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing leptotene

label: prophase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic prophase

label: chromatoid body
definition: A membrane-less, cytoplasmic ribonucleoprotein granule present in neoblasts and germ cells implicated in post-transcriptional regulation. The RNA helicase DHH1/RCK, Tudor, SmB, methylated substrates of PRMT5, PIWI-3 and Germinal Histone H4 localize to chromatoid bodies in neoblasts.

label: multipolar neuron
definition: Neuron with an axon and two or more dendrites.

label: chromosome part
definition: This is a manufactured term, that serves the purpose of allow the parts of a chromosome to have an is_a path to the root.

label: embryonic pharynx neuron
definition: A neuronal cell innervating the embryonic pharynx. Four neurons innervate the radial muscle fibers that ring the oral opening.

label: nuclear inner membrane
definition: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope.

label: cytoplasm
definition: All of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures

label: Stage 5
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 5-7 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis onset. Downregulation of early embryo enriched transcripts and birth of adult lineages within the blastomere population. Early embryonic gut formation continues. Yolk ingestion into the gut cavity.

label: testis lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the testis

label: longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed along the anteroposterior axis. Upon regeneration, these muscles are thought to be established from truncated pre-existing fibers.Inner most body wall muscle fibers arrayed along the anteroposterior axis. These fibers are thicker than the outer longitudinal muscle fibers. The pattern of these muscles differs along the dorsoventral axis, with the dorsal arrangement converging at the central zone of the anterior pole. The ventral arrangement is more parallel or may diverge slightly as it approaches the ventral pole.

label: integumental system
definition: Connected anatomical system that forms a barrier between an animal and its environment. In vertebrates, the integumental system consists of the epidermis, dermis plus associated glands and adnexa such as hair and scales. In invertebrates, the integumental system may include cuticle.

label: meiotic G1 phase spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic G1 phase

label: germ cell cyst
definition: A clonally-related group of interconnected spermatogonial or oogonial cells, enveloped by somatic gonadal cells.

label: peripheral nervous system
definition: A major division of the nervous system that contains nerves which connect the central nervous system (CNS) with sensory organs, other organs, muscles, blood vessels and glands.

label: pharynx outer nerve plexus
definition: Ring of the pharynx nerve plexus that is proximal to the exterior surface.

label: ventral region of the whole animal
definition: Compartment along the dorsoventral axis that is below the anteroposterior axis.

label: posterior muscle cell
definition: muscle cell is contained in the posterior region

label: ventral epidermis cell
definition: cell which is part of the ventral epidermis

label: meiotic metaphase 1 stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic metaphase I

label: anterior region of anterior fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the anterior region of the animal.

label: parapharyngeal cell
definition: cell which is part of the parapharyngeal region

label: terminally differentiated cell
definition: A post-mitotic, terminally differentiated cell type found in planarian embryos, juveniles and/or adult animals.

label: nuclear periphery
definition: The portion of the nuclear lumen proximal to the inner nuclear membrane.

label: septate junction
definition: A cell-cell junction  in invertebrates that seals cells together in an epithelium in a way that prevents even small molecules from leaking from one side of the sheet to the other.

label: cell-cell junction
definition: A cell junction that forms a connection between two or more cells in a multicellular organism; this excludes direct cytoplasmic junctions such as ring canals.

label: GABAergic neuron
definition: Neurons that express glutamine decarboxylase.

label: phagocytic cell
definition: A cell that engulfs large particles or cells via invagination of the plasma membrane and creation of a phagosome.

label: dorsal region of wedge fragment
definition: The dorsal region of a piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: embryonic gut cavity
definition: Cavity encompassed by the embryonic digestive tract, prior to formation of the branched defintive gut.

label: ovary nerve plexus
definition: Nerve plexus surrounding the ovary.

label: cell-cell contact zone
definition: Extended zone of intimate apposition between two cells containing one or more types of intercellular junctions.

label: meiotic metaphase 2 spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic metaphase II

label: zygote
definition: Diploid cell resulting from the fusion of male and female gametes at fertilization. [The_Dictionary_of_Cell_and_Molecular_Biology:Third_Edition ].

label: collecting duct
definition: Non-ciliated tubules associated with the distal tubules, which cross the basement membrane and terminate in the dorsal epidermis.

label: asexual organism
definition: An individual member of the asexual biotype of Schmidtea mediterranea.

label: ventral region of prepharyngeal fragment
definition: The ventral region of a fragment derived from two prepharyngeal amputations, removing the head and posterior regions of the animal.

label: dorsal stripe
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells along the dorsal midline.

label: optic nerve
definition: A neuron projection bundle that connects the retina or its analog in the eye with the brain. This includes the vertebrate optic nerve (not truly a nerve) as well as analogous structures such as the Bolwig nerve in Drosophila.

label: Golgi apparatus
definition: A compound membranous cytoplasmic organelle of eukaryotic cells, consisting of flattened, ribosome-free vesicles arranged in a more or less regular stack. The Golgi apparatus differs from the endoplasmic reticulum in often having slightly thicker membranes, appearing in sections as a characteristic shallow semicircle so that the convex side (cis or entry face) abuts the endoplasmic reticulum, secretory vesicles emerging from the concave side (trans or exit face). In vertebrate cells there is usually one such organelle, while in invertebrates and plants, where they are known usually as dictyosomes, there may be several scattered in the cytoplasm. The Golgi apparatus processes proteins produced on the ribosomes of the rough endoplasmic reticulum; such processing includes modification of the core oligosaccharides of glycoproteins, and the sorting and packaging of proteins for transport to a variety of cellular locations. Three different regions of the Golgi are now recognized both in terms of structure and function: cis, in the vicinity of the cis face, trans, in the vicinity of the trans face, and medial, lying between the cis and trans regions.

label: nuclear part
definition: Any constituent part of the nucleus, a membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated.

label: nuclear lumen
definition: The volume enclosed by the nuclear inner membrane.

label: anterior region of posterior fragment
definition: The anterior region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the posterior region of the animal.

label: brain commissure
definition: any of the nerve fiber tracts that span the longitudinal fissure between the cerebral and/or cerebellar hemispheres of the brain

label: postsynaptic cell
definition: A specialized area of membrane facing the presynaptic membrane on the tip of the nerve ending and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft). Neurotransmitters cross the synaptic cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane.

label: parenchymal cell
definition: cell which is part of the parenchyma

label: ventral midline
definition: The median line/ plane of bilateral symmetry along the anteroposterior axis on the ventral surface of the animal.

label: posterior primary gut branch
definition: The primary gut branches of the triclad gut lateral and posterior to the pharynx and pharyngeal pouch.

label: neural progenitor cell
definition: Neoblasts and their differentiating daughters implicated in maintenance and regeneration of different tissues in the nervous system.

label: central nervous system
definition: The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the neural tube derivatives: the brain and spinal cord. In invertebrates it includes central ganglia plus nerve cord.

label: anterior region of the whole animal
definition: Compartment along the anteroposterior axis closer to the head rather than the tail, from the head margin to the esophagus.

label: regenerating posterior fragment
definition: a posterior fragment that is regenerating

label: medial-lateral axis of the whole animal
definition: Axis that runs from the center of the body, starting at the anteroposterior axis and out to the lateral (left, right, dorsal or ventral) surface of the animal.

label: somatic gonadal cell
definition: A non-germline cell within the ovary or testis.

label: somatic cell
definition: One of the cells of the body that compose the tissues, organs, and parts of that individual other than the germ cells.

label: posterior pole
definition: Distinct posterior cluster of muscle cells located at the midline which express wnt1.

label: longitudinal muscle progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, myoD+, snail-1+ progenitor neoblasts required for specification and creation of longitudinal muscle fibers.

label: anterior pole
definition: Distinct anterior cluster of muscle cells located at the midline which express notum, follistatin, zic-1, and foxD.

label: early female germ cell
definition: A premeiotic female germ cell (i.e., a diploid female germline stem cell or transit amplifying oogonial cell).

label: ovary lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the ovary

label: tuba
definition: A sperm storage organ located immediately posterior to the ovary, at the anterior end of the oviduct. Oocytes exiting the ovary are fertilized in the tuba as they enter the oviduct.

label: nerve plexus
definition: Anatomical junction where subdivisions of two or more neural trees interconnect with one another to form a network through which nerve fibers of the constituent nerve trees become regrouped; together with other nerve plexuses, nerves and ganglia, it constitutes the peripheral nervous system. Examples: cervical nerve plexus, brachial nerve plexus, sacral nerve plexus[FMA].

label: dorsal region of tail
definition: The dorsal region of the tail.

label: meiotic anaphase I stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic anaphase I

label: primitive gut cell
definition: A phagocytic cell closely associated with the embryonic pharynx.

label: oogonial cell
definition: An undifferentiated germ cell that proliferates rapidly and gives rise to oocytes.

label: body wall musculature
definition: Any collection of muscles that is part of a body wall [Automatically generated definition].

label: rough endoplasmic reticulum
definition: Network of interconnected, flattened, and/or tubular membrane, known as cisternae. This membrane is contiguous with the outer nuclear membrane. The endoplasmic reticulum is involved in both protein and lipid synthesis.

label: organelle membrane
definition: A membrane that is one of the two lipid bilayers of an organelle envelope or the outermost membrane of single membrane bound organelle.

label: pharynx tip
definition: The distal-most end of the pharnyx containing an opening to the pharynx lumen.

label: pharynx epithelial cell
definition: epithelial cell which is part of the pharynx

label: prepharyngeal midline
definition: The center-most region just anterior to the pharynx

label: sagittal plane of the whole animal
definition: Anatomical plane which divides the body into right and left parts. This plane passes through the midline at the midline but does not always the midline.

label: X2 cell
definition: A sorted cell population containing irradiation-sensitive and irradiation-insensitive cells, characterized by weak Hoescht 33342 and calcein-AM staining. X2 cell populations contain neoblasts as well as a variety of lineage-dedicated post-mitotic progenitor cells.

label: fission fragment
definition: A fragment derived from a spontaneous or induced fission event.

label: dorsal epidermis cell
definition: cell which is part of the dorsal region of the epidermis

label: extraembryonic organ
definition: Organ that is associated with an embryo and derived from the zygote from which it develops, but which does not contribute to the embryo proper or to structures that are part of the same organism after embryogenesis.

label: anterior region of plug fragment
definition: The anterior region of a 3D piece of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: releasing gland cell
definition: Specialized insunk epithelial cell that is part of the adhesion gland which is responsible for production of releasing substance.

label: embryonic pharynx radial muscle cell
definition: Differentiated radial muscle cell present in the embryonic pharynx.

label: regenerating prepharyngeal fragment
definition: a prepharyngeal fragment that is regenerating

label: extraembryonic cell
definition: Post-mitotic, terminally differentiated cells which, give rise to temporary embryonic tissues.

label: organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton, and prokaryotic structures such as anammoxosomes and pirellulosomes. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: axon
definition: The long process of a neuron that conducts nerve impulses, usually away from the cell body to the terminals and varicosities, which are sites of storage and release of neurotransmitter.

label: secretory vesicle
definition: A cytoplasmic, membrane bound vesicle that is capable of fusing to the plasma membrane to release its contents into the extracellular space.

label: vitelline gland
definition: Glands surrounding the oviducts which produce yolk cells. Yolk cells deposited into the oviducts travel to the genital atrium where they are packaged, along with one or more zygotes, into developing egg capsules.

label: intracellular membrane-bounded organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane and occurring within the cell. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: antrum
definition: A chamber formation in an organ.

label: TrpA+ central nervous system neuron
definition: A subset of TrpA+ neurons, located medially in the cephalic ganglia, whose formation is dependent on function of runt-1 and ap2.

label: non ciliated epithelial cell
definition: An epithelial cell lacking cilia.

label: longitudinal region
definition: A region bounded by any sagittal plane though the animal and the left or right side of the animal. NOTE: sagittal plane is an anatomical plane that divides a bilateral body into left and right parts, not necessarily of even size

label: telophase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic telophase

label: chemical pharynx amputation
definition: Amputation of the phaynx, including the esophagus, by treatment with Sodium Azide.

label: diagonal muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed diagonally along the anteroposterior axis.

label: meiotic anaphase II spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic anaphase II

label: diakinesis stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing diakinesis

label: linear incision
definition: A breach of the epidermis and optionally down into other structures though an insult with a knife or other instrument, such that the movement includes the z direction and one or more of the x y direction.

label: prophase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic prophase

label: X1 cell
definition: A sorted cell population enriched for irradiation-sensitive, cycling cells (4n cells, with high levels of Hoescht 33342 staining) with scant cytoplasm (low levels of calcein-AM staining). X1 cells are enriched for cycling neoblasts.

label: cephalic ganglia neuron
definition: A central nervous system neuron located within the planarian brain.

label: intestinal phagocyte
definition: Absorptive digestive cells that engulf food particles for intracellular digestion.

label: synapse
definition: The junction between a nerve fiber of one neuron and another neuron, muscle fiber or glial cell. As the nerve fiber approaches the synapse it enlarges into a specialized structure, the presynaptic nerve ending, which contains mitochondria and synaptic vesicles. At the tip of the nerve ending is the presynaptic membrane; facing it, and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft) is a specialized area of membrane on the receiving cell, known as the postsynaptic membrane. In response to the arrival of nerve impulses, the presynaptic nerve ending secretes molecules of neurotransmitters into the synaptic cleft. These diffuse across the cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane.

label: meiotic germ cell
definition: A germ cell undergoing meiosis.

label: pharynx progenitor cell
definition: foxA1+ neoblasts and their post-mitotic, differentiating daughters required for maintenance and regeneration of the pharynx.

label: epithelial cell component
definition: A part of an epithelial cell.

label: submuscular nerve plexus
definition: Plexus of nerves that innervate the body wall musculature.

label: metaphase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: embryonic pharynx lumen epithelial surface
definition: The epithelial cell surface lining the embryonic pharynx lumen.

label: syncytium
definition: An anatomical entity consisting of a single or a few multinucleated structures

label: cephalic ganglia
definition: The planarian brain, consisting of two bilaterally symmetric lobes occupying a ventral position in the head.

label: anaphase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: embryonic gut cell surface
definition: The surface of phagocytic embryonic gut cells in contact with ingested yolk cells.

label: posterior region of posterior fragment
definition: The posterior region of a fragment encompassing all or part of the posterior region of the animal.

label: regenerating anterior fragment
definition: a anterior fragment that is regenerating

label: ribosome
definition: An intracellular organelle, about 200 A in diameter, consisting of RNA and protein. It is the site of protein biosynthesis resulting from translation of messenger RNA (mRNA). It consists of two subunits, one large and one small, each containing only protein and RNA. Both the ribosome and its subunits are characterized by their sedimentation coefficients, expressed in Svedberg units (symbol: S). Hence, the prokaryotic ribosome (70S) comprises a large (50S) subunit and a small (30S) subunit, while the eukaryotic ribosome (80S) comprises a large (60S) subunit and a small (40S) subunit. Two sites on the ribosomal large subunit are involved in translation, namely the aminoacyl site (A site) and peptidyl site (P site). Ribosomes from prokaryotes, eukaryotes, mitochondria, and chloroplasts have characteristically distinct ribosomal proteins. [ https://www.worldcat.org/search?q=bn%3A0198506732 ]

label: linear amputation
definition: An amputation performed with a transverse, oblique or longitudinal cut.

label: neuron projection bundle
definition: A fasciculated bundle of neuron projections (GO:0043005), largely or completely lacking synapses.

label: posterior region of the whole animal
definition: Three dimensional compartment along the anteroposterior axis that is closer to the tail rather than the head, from the anterior boundary of the pharyngeal pouch to the tip of the tail.

label: neoblast
definition: A heterogeneous population of pluripotent, somatic adult stem cells and lineage primed progenitors that are required for maintenance and regeneration of all cell types in planaria, including the germline.

label: epithelial cell
definition: A cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface. The cell has a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and for cell polarity where the apical part is directed towards the lumen and the basal part to the basal lamina.

label: ommochrome pigment cell
definition: Parenchymal cells that synthesize and contain brown ommonchrome pigment.

label: membrane-bounded organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: ommochrome pigment granule
definition: pigment granule which is part of the ommochrome pigment cell

label: musculature system
definition: Total musculature of the planarian body.
